<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Sizing considerations for AWS deployment</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 4 minutes to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>The performance information provided here is for your reference only. Your implementation may consume more resources or require more resources to perform in an acceptable manner. For example, when running a tailored version of Operations Bridge, the resources may need to be adjusted.
</p><p>We recommend that you&nbsp;<a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://aws.amazon.com/documentation/cloudwatch/">keep monitoring</a>&nbsp;the system resource usage and adjust the sizing configurations according to the actual usage.
</p>
<div class="Admonition_Note">
<p><span class="autonumber">Note: </span>
The recommendations should be considered as the minimum requirements for running Operations Bridge properly.
</p>
</div>
