<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Suite_size_definitions">Suite size definitions</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SizRecoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Suite size definitions">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SizRecoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Suite size definitions">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>When you run the suite installer to install Operations Bridge, you will need to select a suite size: Small, Medium, or Large. Different suite sizes require different hardware configurations. For more information, see the sizing recommendations in <a href="./itom/Hybrid_Cloud_Management:2018.11/Install_on-premises/Plan/Deployment_architecture" title="Hybrid Cloud Management:2018.11/Install on-premises/Plan/Deployment architecture">Plan the deployment</a> section.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sizing_for_non-HA_deployment">Sizing for non-HA deployment</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SizRecoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Sizing for non-HA deployment">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SizRecoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Sizing for non-HA deployment">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The following table lists the minimum resources needed for setting up an Operations Bridge environment on AWS without consideration for high availability. <br>A standard deployment includes master nodes, worker nodes, an NFS server (for storage) and databases.<br>
For the disk storage volume type, if not specified, <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/EBSVolumeTypes.html">GP2 SSD</a>*** is used by default on AWS.
</p>
