<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sizing_for_HA_deployment">Sizing for HA deployment</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SizRecoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=3" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Sizing for HA deployment">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SizRecoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Sizing for HA deployment">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The following table lists the minimum resources needed for setting an Operations Bridge environment in the cloud with consideration for high availability. While 3 worker nodes are listed as the minimum, it is <b>highly recommended</b> that 4 worker nodes be implemented to ensure an HA environment.
</p>
<a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);"><button class="flscrbtn"><i class="material-icons flscricn">open_in_new</i><div style="margin: auto 5px;">View Fullscreen</div></button></a><table>

